Description:
   Gap Hold is a foundational concealment technique for the Cipher. The
   operative identifies a tactical gap — a blind spot, shadow, or structural
   feature of the environment — and uses it to maintain a concealed position
   without full stealth movement. Unlike active sneak, Gap Hold is a passive
   ability that allows the Cipher to remain hidden while stationary.

   The technique is most effective in complex terrain where environmental
   features provide natural cover. A Cipher using Gap Hold can observe
   enemies without being observed themselves, setting up ambushes or
   gathering information before engaging. The hold breaks if the Cipher
   moves or takes any aggressive action.
